                <note rend="inline" type="source">816.00/10–2344: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in El Salvador</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gade</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">San Salvador</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-10-23T16:00:00-06:00"
                            >October 23, 1944—4 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 7:45 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>342. I have today received a note from the new Foreign Minister Reyes Arrieta
                    Rossi announcing the resignation of General Menéndez as President and the
                    assumption of office by Colonel Aguirre. No reply is being made pending
                    instructions from the Department.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Gade</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
